A 76-year-old woman sustained minor injuries after she rolled her vehicle on CR Swart Road at about 10.30am this morning, north of Joburg, Roodepoort Record reports. READ MORE: Kuga burns out north of Joburg Curious bystanders inspect the vehicle. (Photo: Supplied) It is alleged that she was travelling from the direction of Ontdekkers Road when the lower front control arm of her vehicle broke causing the vehicle to overturn near the intersection with Naboom Street. She sustained only minor injuries but was taken to hospital due to her age. More updates to follow. Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.